  "_meta": {
    "version": 1,
    "purpose": "Curated state-lobbying seed mappings: known major corporate lobbyists in CA / NY / TX / NYC with publicly disclosed annual spend. Used as the fallback corpus when the live Socrata / CSV pulls are unavailable or rate-limited.",
    "methodology": "Entries are seeded from publicly reported state filings (CA Secretary of State CalAccess, NY COELIG Bi-Monthly Reports, TX Ethics Commission lobby search, NYC eLobbyist). Each entry has a primary source URL. Spend figures are conservative annual approximations (rounded to nearest $100K) based on most recent publicly available filings (2023-2024 reporting years). Issue areas are short tags taken from each filer's stated lobbying subject codes.",
    "sources": {
      "ca": "https://calaccess.sos.ca.gov/Lobbying/Employers/",
      "ny": "https://opendata.ny.gov/Government-Finance/Lobbying-Bi-Monthly-Reports/",
      "tx": "https://www.ethics.state.tx.us/data/search/lobby/",
      "nyc": "https://data.cityofnewyork.us/City-Government/Lobbyist-Search/2vxx-r373"
    },
    "severity_rationale": "State lobbying alone is neither inherently negative nor positive. Disclosure is required by law and many of these entries reflect routine government affairs. Severity is MIXED for narrative; sc enum is left unset so the existing exec-political-donations writer remains the canonical source for the political-money sc."
